<P>In which the Re&s;i&s;tance, Weight, Solidity, Activity, Vitality, and other gene|ral Properties of Fo&s;&s;ile, Vegetable, and Animal Bodies, will be experimen|tally accounted for; and the Phaenomena of Light and Colours, Fire, Heat, Electricity, Magneti&s;m, and the various Revolutions of the Planetary Sy&s;|tem, &s;hewn to be the mechanical Effects of mere Motion. To be comprized in a Cour&s;e of Six Lectures.</P>
<P>By WILLIAM KENRICK. <HI>Juris utriu&s;que et Philo&s;ophiae Doctor.</HI></P>
<Q>Omnis enim philo&s;ophiae difficultas in eo ver&s;ari videtur ut a phaenomenis motuum inve&s;tigemus vires naturae; deinde ab his viribus demon&s;tremus phaenomena re|liqua: quibus viribus ignotis, philo&s;ophi hactenus naturam fru&s;tra tentarunt.
<BIBL>Sir ISAAC NEWTON.</BIBL></Q>
<P>&tristar; As the&s;e Lectures will be delivered in a popular Style, dive&s;ted as much as po&s;&s;ible of technical Terms, and elucidated by familiar Experiments, to accommo|date them to Per&s;ons unacquainted with the Mathematical Sciences; Ladies as well as Gentlemen will, by de&s;ire, be admitted. As it will be nece&s;&s;ary al&s;o, in Aid of the Memory, to furni&s;h the Auditors with printed Copies of each Lecture, as it is delivered; it is pre&s;umed they would wi&s;h to indemnify the Lecturer in the Expence of the Impre&s;&s;ion. It is propo&s;ed therefore, to &s;ub&s;cribe the Whole, illu&s;trated with the nece&s;&s;ary Copper-plates, at the Price of One Guinea; Half to be paid on &s;ub&s;crib|ing, and the other Half on the Delivery of the third Lecture. Tickets of Admit|tance to the Recital will be &s;ent <HI>Gratis</HI> to the Sub&s;cribers, on &s;ending their Addre&s;s to the Author or the Publi&s;her.</P>
